  "text": "LibreOffice Calc's formula evaluation follows a multi-stage pipeline:\n\n1. **Formula Compilation (Tokenization)**: The ScCompiler class (sc/inc/compiler.hxx, sc/source/core/tool/compiler.cxx) parses formula strings and converts them into token arrays. It handles formula grammar conventions, reference parsing, and function name resolution.\n\n2. **Formula Interpretation (Evaluation)**: The ScInterpreter class (sc/source/core/inc/interpre.hxx, sc/source/core/tool/interpr1-8.cxx) executes the compiled token array. The Interpret() method is the primary entry point that evaluates formulas by processing opcodes and maintaining a computation stack.\n\n3. **Formula Cell Storage**: The ScFormulaCell class (sc/inc/formulacell.hxx, sc/source/core/data/formulacell.cxx) represents a single cell containing a formula. It stores the compiled token array (pCode), the cached result (aResult), and flags for tracking dirty state and recalculation requirements.\n\n4. **Recalculation Management**: The ScDocument class (sc/inc/document.hxx) manages recalculation through:\n   - HardRecalcState enum: Tracks recalculation state (OFF, TEMPORARY, ETERNAL)\n   - CalcAll() method: Orchestrates full document recalculation\n   - Broadcast/Listener mechanism: The ScBroadcastAreaSlot class (sc/source/core/data/bcaslot.cxx) manages which cells depend on changed cells through broadcast areas, ensuring only affected cells are marked dirty for recalculation.\n\nFor a formula like =SUM(A1:A10):\n1. Compiler tokenizes it into opcodes for SUM and the range reference\n2. Formula cell stores the token array\n3. When evaluated, Interpreter executes the SUM opcode\n4. If A1:A10 changes, broadcast areas notify dependent cells\n5. Dirty flags trigger recalculation on next CalcAll()"
}

